Design on Building Data Exchange System for Railway Intermodal Transport

HUANG Minzhen, WANG Ruimin, SHI Ling, XU Wenrong (Institute of Computing Technology, China Academy of Railway Sciences Corporation Limited, Beijing 100081, China)
Abstract: Intermodal transport is an efficient way of organizing freight transport, which is of an important role and great significance in reducing cost, promoting green development, enriching transport services, improving economic benefits and operation efficiency, expanding the range of economic radiation and regional development, linking the modern industrial chain and supply chain, and supporting the Belt and Road Initiative. Through the study on the current situation of intermodal transport in China and the elaboration of water-rail and road-rail intermodal transport, the overall and technical architecture of the data exchange platform for intermodal transport are proposed and various functions of the data exchange platform are developed, involving aspects of freight data processing center, intermodal transport data exchange, data transmission control, comprehensive application, operation and maintenance, etc. The aim is to realize information sharing and exchange in terms of water-rail and road-rail intermodal transport, improve the level of logistics as a whole and the capability of coordinating business, establish an information chain of whole-process logistics, and lay a foundation for realizing“one-waybill system”in the future intermodal transport. Keywords: belt and road initiative; intermodal transport; whole-process logistics; one-waybill system; water-rail intermodal transport; road-rail intermodal transport

